On 7/23/03 9:21 AM, "Dave Newman" <dnewman(-at-)indy.rr.com> wrote:

> Can I use the left (driver's) side tie rod assembly for both sides?  I'm
> getting ready to order new ones and it appears that Bus Depot offers the
> left complete assembly only.

The driver's side (LHD) is non-adjustable and the passenger side is
adjustable.

It's correct to have one of each but you could use two adjustable ones. If
you put on two non-adjustable tie-rods I don't see how you are going to be
able to get the correct wheel toe.

> Will this make alignment more complicated?  I plan on doing a rough
> alignment before taking it to the shop.

They have both...

Tie Rod With Ends  
Adjustable
211415801F

Tie Rod With Ends  
Non-Adjustable
211415802F

...all of the vendor catalogs seem to use left and right in their
descriptions of those items as if you are looking at the front of the bus.

